psa.2.text:
Let me tell of the decree:
YHWH said to me, "You are my son;
today I have begotten you.

psa.3.text:
Rise up, YHWH! Save me, my God!
For you strike all my enemies on the cheek;
you break the teeth of the wicked.

Rescue belongs to YHWH;
your blessing is on your people.
Selah

psa.56.text:
My watchful foes hound me all day long;
many fight against me
from their proud height.

In God, whose word I praise —
in God I trust, I will not fear;
what can mere flesh do to me?

All day long they twist my words;
every scheme of theirs against me
bends toward evil.

You have counted my every wandering;
put my tears in your flask —
are they not written in your book?

Then my enemies will turn back
on the day I call to you;
this I know: God is for me.

psa.57.text:
He will send from heaven and save me;
he rebukes the one who hounds me. Selah.
God will send his steadfast love and his faithfulness.

psa.59.text:
For look — they lie in wait for my life;
fierce men band together against me,
for no transgression or sin of mine, YHWH.

You, YHWH, God of hosts, God of Israel —
rouse yourself to punish all the nations;
show no mercy to villains who plot evil. Selah.

Do not kill them, lest my people forget;
scatter them by your power and bring them down,
O Lord, our shield.

For the sin of their mouths, the words of their lips,
let them be caught in their pride,
for the cursing and lies they utter.

But I will sing of your strength;
I will sing aloud of your steadfast love in the morning,
for you have been my fortress,
a refuge in the day of my distress.

O my strength, I will sing praise to you,
for God is my fortress,
my God of steadfast love.

psa.60.text:
God has spoken in his holiness — I will exult;
I will divide up Shechem,
and measure out the Valley of Succoth.

Gilead is mine, Manasseh is mine;
Ephraim is my helmet, my strength;
Judah is my scepter.

Moab is my washbasin;
upon Edom I cast my sandal;
over Philistia I shout in triumph.

psa.61.text:
From the end of the earth I call to you
when my heart grows faint;
lead me to the rock that is higher than I.

psa.62.text:
Trust in him at all times, O people;
pour out your heart before him —
God is a refuge for us. Selah.

Put no trust in extortion,
no vain hope in robbery;
if riches increase, set not your heart on them.

Once God has spoken;
twice have I heard this:
that strength belongs to God,

psa.63.text:
But the king shall rejoice in God;
all who swear by him shall glory,
for the mouths of liars will be stopped.

psa.64.text:
They hold fast to their evil purpose;
they talk of laying snares in secret,
saying, "Who can see us?"

Then all mankind will fear;
they will tell what God has done,
and ponder what he has wrought.

psa.65.text:
You visit the earth and water it;
you greatly enrich it;
the river of God is full of water;
you provide their grain,
for so you have prepared the earth.

psa.66.text:
All the earth worships you
and sings praises to you;
they sing praises to your name. Selah.

He turned the sea into dry land;
they passed through the river on foot —
there did we rejoice in him,

you let men ride over our heads;
we went through fire and through water,
yet you brought us out to a place of abundance.

I will offer to you burnt offerings of fattened animals,
with the smoke of the sacrifice of rams;
I will make an offering of bulls and goats. Selah.

psa.68.text:
As smoke is driven away, drive them away;
as wax melts before fire,
let the wicked perish before God.

But let the righteous be glad;
let them exult before God;
let them be jubilant with joy.

Sing to God, sing praises to his name;
lift up a song to him who rides through the deserts —
YHWH is his name; exult before him.

God settles the solitary in a home;
he leads out the prisoners to prosperity,
but the rebellious dwell in a parched land.

The chariots of God are twice ten thousand,
thousands upon thousands;
the Lord is among them, as at Sinai, in his holy place.

Blessed be the Lord,
who daily bears us up;
God is our salvation. Selah.

Our God is a God of salvation;
and to YHWH, the Lord,
belongs escape from death.

Awesome is God from his sanctuary;
the God of Israel — he gives power and strength to his people.
Blessed be God.

psa.69.text:
I sink in deep mire, where there is no foothold;
I have come into deep waters,
and the flood sweeps over me.

Let not those who hope in you be put to shame through me,
O Lord YHWH of hosts;
let not those who seek you be brought to dishonor through me,
O God of Israel.

Deliver me from sinking in the mire;
let me be delivered from those who hate me
and from the deep waters.

Reproach has broken my heart, and I am in despair;
I looked for pity, but there was none,
and for comforters, but I found none.

For God will save Zion
and build up the cities of Judah,
and they shall dwell there and possess it;
